# Google Analytics 4 measurement ID. Get this from
# https://analytics.google.com/ → Admin → your property →
# Data streams → your web stream → "Measurement ID"
# (looks like G-XXXXXXXXXX).
#
# Vite only exposes env vars prefixed with `VITE_` to the
# client bundle. The ID is safe to commit in code; it's a
# public identifier (also known as the "G-ID" or "tag ID").
# The actual tracking-data API key is handled server-side
# by Google.
#
# In production (Vercel), set this as a project environment
# variable:
#   Vercel project → Settings → Environment Variables →
#   add VITE_GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID = G-XXXXXXXXXX (Production)
#
# In development, leave this commented out and analytics
# will be a no-op (a console warning will fire if you load
# the production build without the ID set).
# VITE_GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
